{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"When I go to parties,"},{"time":1575,"text":"it doesn't usually take very long"},{"time":3359,"text":"for people to find out"},{"time":4399,"text":"that I'm a scientist and I study sex."},{"time":7507,"text":"And then I get asked questions."},{"time":12408,"text":"And the questions usually have a very particular format."},{"time":15575,"text":"They start with the phrase,"},{"time":16807,"text":"\"A friend told me,\""},{"time":18708,"text":"and then they end with the phrase,"},{"time":20608,"text":"\"Is this true?\""},{"time":22525,"text":"And most of the time"},{"time":23911,"text":"I'm glad to say that I can answer them,"},{"time":26030,"text":"but sometimes I have to say,"},{"time":27877,"text":"\"I'm really sorry,"},{"time":29010,"text":"but I don't know"},{"time":30194,"text":"because I'm not that kind of a doctor.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":33278,"text":"That is, I'm not a clinician,"},{"time":35194,"text":"I'm a comparative biologist who studies anatomy."},{"time":38385,"text":"And my job is to look at lots of different species of animals"},{"time":41318,"text":"and try to figure out how their tissues and organs work"},{"time":44635,"text":"when everything's going right,"},{"time":46136,"text":"rather than trying to figure out"},{"time":47754,"text":"how to fix things when they go wrong,"},{"time":49337,"text":"like so many of you."},{"time":50538,"text":"And what I do is I look for similarities and differences"},{"time":52937,"text":"in the solutions that they've evolved"},{"time":55204,"text":"for fundamental biological problems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":56788,"text":"So today I'm here to argue"},{"time":58637,"text":"that this is not at all"},{"time":62503,"text":"an esoteric Ivory Tower activity"},{"time":64404,"text":"that we find at our universities,"},{"time":65721,"text":"but that broad study"},{"time":67704,"text":"across species, tissue types and organ systems"},{"time":70656,"text":"can produce insights"},{"time":72291,"text":"that have direct implications for human health."},{"time":75675,"text":"And this is true both of my recent project"},{"time":78173,"text":"on sex differences in the brain,"},{"time":79897,"text":"and my more mature work"},{"time":81816,"text":"on the anatomy and function of penises."},{"time":84650,"text":"And now you know why I'm fun at parties."}]},{"cues":[{"time":87280,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":88248,"text":"So today I'm going to give you an example"},{"time":90531,"text":"drawn from my penis study"},{"time":92248,"text":"to show you how knowledge"},{"time":93865,"text":"drawn from studies of one organ system"},{"time":95632,"text":"provided insights into a very different one."},{"time":98613,"text":"Now I'm sure as everyone in the audience already knows --"},{"time":101631,"text":"I did have to explain it to my nine-year-old late last week --"},{"time":105147,"text":"penises are structures that transfer sperm"},{"time":108898,"text":"from one individual to another."},{"time":110198,"text":"And the slide behind me"},{"time":111698,"text":"barely scratches the surface"},{"time":113431,"text":"of how widespread they are in animals."},{"time":115396,"text":"There's an enormous amount of anatomical variation."},{"time":117381,"text":"You find muscular tubes, modified legs, modified fins,"},{"time":121255,"text":"as well as the mammalian fleshy, inflatable cylinder"},{"time":125101,"text":"that we're all familiar with --"},{"time":126736,"text":"or at least half of you are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129018,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":131419,"text":"And I think we see this tremendous variation"},{"time":134157,"text":"because it's a really effective solution"},{"time":137308,"text":"to a very basic biological problem,"},{"time":139474,"text":"and that is getting sperm in a position"},{"time":141957,"text":"to meet up with eggs and form zygotes."},{"time":144509,"text":"Now the penis isn't actually required for internal fertiliztion,"},{"time":148458,"text":"but when internal fertilization evolves,"},{"time":150924,"text":"penises often follow."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152924,"text":"And the question I get when I start talking about this most often is,"},{"time":157341,"text":"\"What made you interested in this subject?\""},{"time":160257,"text":"And the answer is skeletons."},{"time":164207,"text":"You wouldn't think that skeletons and penises"},{"time":166774,"text":"have very much to do with one another."},{"time":168625,"text":"And that's because we tend to think of skeletons"},{"time":170757,"text":"as stiff lever systems"},{"time":172407,"text":"that produce speed or power."},{"time":174090,"text":"And my first forays into biological research,"},{"time":177657,"text":"doing dinosaur paleontology as an undergraduate,"},{"time":180475,"text":"were really squarely in that realm."}]},{"cues":[{"time":182026,"text":"But when I went to graduate school to study biomechanics,"},{"time":185143,"text":"I really wanted to find a dissertation project"},{"time":187608,"text":"that would expand our knowledge of skeletal function."},{"time":190507,"text":"I tried a bunch of different stuff."},{"time":192309,"text":"A lot of it didn't pan out."},{"time":193957,"text":"But then one day I started thinking"},{"time":195791,"text":"about the mammalian penis."},{"time":197573,"text":"And it's really an odd sort of structure."},{"time":201591,"text":"Before it can be used for internal fertilization,"},{"time":204408,"text":"its mechanical behavior has to change"},{"time":205891,"text":"in a really dramatic fashion."},{"time":207608,"text":"Most of the time it's a flexible organ."},{"time":210206,"text":"It's easy to bend."},{"time":211490,"text":"But before it's brought into use"},{"time":213484,"text":"during copulation"},{"time":214702,"text":"it has to become rigid,"},{"time":216460,"text":"it has to become difficult to bend."},{"time":218475,"text":"And moreover, it has to work."},{"time":220492,"text":"A reproductive system that fails to function"},{"time":223242,"text":"produces an individual that has no offspring,"},{"time":226557,"text":"and that individual is then kicked out of the gene pool."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229728,"text":"And so I thought, \"Here's a problem"},{"time":232189,"text":"that just cries out for a skeletal system --"},{"time":235437,"text":"not one like this one,"},{"time":238649,"text":"but one like this one --"},{"time":241706,"text":"because, functionally,"},{"time":244123,"text":"a skeleton is any system"},{"time":245690,"text":"that supports tissue and transmits forces."},{"time":248722,"text":"And I already knew that animals like this earthworm,"},{"time":251072,"text":"indeed most animals,"},{"time":252518,"text":"don't support their tissues"},{"time":253811,"text":"by draping them over bones."},{"time":255605,"text":"Instead they're more like reinforced water balloons."},{"time":258438,"text":"They use a skeleton that we call a hydrostatic skeleton."},{"time":262305,"text":"And a hydrostatic skeleton"},{"time":264371,"text":"uses two elements."},{"time":266289,"text":"The skeletal support comes from an interaction"},{"time":268439,"text":"between a pressurized fluid"},{"time":270213,"text":"and a surrounding wall of tissue"},{"time":271819,"text":"that's held in tension and reinforced with fibrous proteins."},{"time":276290,"text":"And the interaction is crucial."},{"time":278538,"text":"Without both elements you have no support."},{"time":281906,"text":"If you have fluid"},{"time":283188,"text":"with no wall to surround it"},{"time":285222,"text":"and keep pressure up,"},{"time":286656,"text":"you have a puddle."},{"time":288560,"text":"And if you have just the wall"},{"time":290660,"text":"with no fluid inside of it to put the wall in tension,"},{"time":292394,"text":"you've got a little wet rag."}]},{"cues":[{"time":294344,"text":"When you look at a penis in cross section,"},{"time":296976,"text":"it has a lot of the hallmarks"},{"time":299409,"text":"of a hydrostatic skeleton."},{"time":301459,"text":"It has a central space"},{"time":302968,"text":"of spongy erectile tissue"},{"time":304488,"text":"that fills with fluid -- in this case blood --"},{"time":307066,"text":"surrounded by a wall of tissue"},{"time":309465,"text":"that's rich in a stiff structural protein called collagen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":313316,"text":"But at the time when I started this project,"},{"time":315816,"text":"the best explanation I could find for penal erection"},{"time":319017,"text":"was that the wall surrounded these spongy tissues,"},{"time":323301,"text":"and the spongy tissues filled with blood"},{"time":325000,"text":"and pressure rose and voila! it became erect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":328268,"text":"And that explained to me expansion --"},{"time":332233,"text":"made sense: more fluid, you get tissues that expand --"},{"time":335800,"text":"but it didn't actually explain erection."},{"time":338817,"text":"Because there was no mechanism in this explanation"},{"time":342708,"text":"for making this structure hard to bend."},{"time":345675,"text":"And no one had systematically looked at the wall tissue."},{"time":348391,"text":"So I thought, wall tissue's important in skeletons."},{"time":350993,"text":"It has to be part of the explanation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":353359,"text":"And this was the point"},{"time":355894,"text":"at which my graduate adviser said,"},{"time":358491,"text":"\"Whoa! Hold on. Slow down.\""},{"time":361874,"text":"Because after about six months of me talking about this,"},{"time":365242,"text":"I think he finally figured out"},{"time":366558,"text":"that I was really serious about the penis thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":369607,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":372654,"text":"So he sat me down, and he warned me."},{"time":374703,"text":"He was like, \"Be careful going down this path."},{"time":376879,"text":"I'm not sure this project's going to pan out.\""},{"time":379646,"text":"Because he was afraid I was walking into a trap."},{"time":382178,"text":"I was taking on a socially embarrassing question"},{"time":386995,"text":"with an answer that he thought"},{"time":389330,"text":"might not be particularly interesting."},{"time":391712,"text":"And that was because"},{"time":393245,"text":"every hydrostatic skeleton"},{"time":394763,"text":"that we had found in nature up to that point"},{"time":396831,"text":"had the same basic elements."},{"time":398628,"text":"It had the central fluid,"},{"time":399845,"text":"it had the surrounding wall,"},{"time":401645,"text":"and the reinforcing fibers in the wall"},{"time":404781,"text":"were arranged in crossed helices"},{"time":407199,"text":"around the long axis of the skeleton."}]},{"cues":[{"time":409256,"text":"So the image behind me"},{"time":410577,"text":"shows a piece of tissue"},{"time":412206,"text":"in one of these cross helical skeletons"},{"time":414231,"text":"cut so that you're looking at the surface of the wall."},{"time":416764,"text":"The arrow shows you the long axis."},{"time":418482,"text":"And you can see two layers of fibers,"},{"time":420332,"text":"one in blue and one in yellow,"},{"time":422033,"text":"arranged in left-handed and right-handed angles."},{"time":424831,"text":"And if you weren't just looking at a little section of the fibers,"},{"time":427080,"text":"those fibers would be going in helices"},{"time":429781,"text":"around the long axis of the skeleton --"},{"time":431531,"text":"something like a Chinese finger trap,"},{"time":433664,"text":"where you stick your fingers in and they get stuck."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435565,"text":"And these skeletons have a particular set of behaviors,"},{"time":438648,"text":"which I'm going to demonstrate in a film."},{"time":440680,"text":"It's a model skeleton"},{"time":441831,"text":"that I made out of a piece of cloth"},{"time":444014,"text":"that I wrapped around an inflated balloon."},{"time":446567,"text":"The cloth's cut on the bias."},{"time":448265,"text":"So you can see that the fibers wrap in helices,"},{"time":451014,"text":"and those fibers can reorient as the skeleton moves,"},{"time":455326,"text":"which means the skeleton's flexible."},{"time":456755,"text":"It lengthens, shortens and bends really easily"},{"time":459228,"text":"in response to internal or external forces."}]},{"cues":[{"time":462775,"text":"Now my adviser's concern"},{"time":464071,"text":"was what if the penile wall tissue"},{"time":466437,"text":"is just the same as any other hydrostatic skeleton."},{"time":468111,"text":"What are you going to contribute?"},{"time":470038,"text":"What new thing are you contributing"},{"time":471505,"text":"to our knowledge of biology?"},{"time":473153,"text":"And I thought, \"Yeah, he does have a really good point here.\""},{"time":476571,"text":"So I spent a long, long time thinking about it."},{"time":478321,"text":"And one thing kept bothering me,"},{"time":480455,"text":"and that's, when they're functioning,"},{"time":482905,"text":"penises don't wiggle."},{"time":484838,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":487177,"text":"So something interesting had to be going on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":490078,"text":"So I went ahead, collected wall tissue,"},{"time":493379,"text":"prepared it so it was erect,"},{"time":494978,"text":"sectioned it, put it on slides"},{"time":497177,"text":"and then stuck it under the microscope to have a look,"},{"time":499829,"text":"fully expecting to see crossed helices of collagen of some variety."},{"time":504865,"text":"But instead I saw this."},{"time":507263,"text":"There's an outer layer and an inner layer."},{"time":510264,"text":"The arrow shows you the long axis of the skeleton."}]},{"cues":[{"time":512814,"text":"I was really surprised at this."},{"time":515383,"text":"Everyone I showed it"},{"time":516328,"text":"was really surprised at this."},{"time":517528,"text":"Why was everyone surprised at this?"},{"time":519065,"text":"That's because we knew theoretically"},{"time":522049,"text":"that there was another way"},{"time":524864,"text":"of arranging fibers in a hydrostatic skeleton,"},{"time":527898,"text":"and that was with fibers at zero degrees"},{"time":530169,"text":"and 90 degrees to the long axis of the structure."},{"time":534035,"text":"The thing is, no one had ever seen it before in nature."},{"time":537597,"text":"And now I was looking at one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":540297,"text":"Those fibers in that particular orientation"},{"time":543031,"text":"give the skeleton a very, very different behavior."},{"time":546246,"text":"I'm going to show a model"},{"time":547431,"text":"made out of exactly the same materials."},{"time":549376,"text":"So it'll be made of the same cotton cloth,"},{"time":551434,"text":"same balloon, same internal pressure."},{"time":554723,"text":"But the only difference"},{"time":557190,"text":"is that the fibers are arranged differently."},{"time":559572,"text":"And you'll see that, unlike the cross helical model,"},{"time":562223,"text":"this model resists extension and contraction"},{"time":565173,"text":"and resists bending."}]},{"cues":[{"time":566624,"text":"Now what that tells us"},{"time":567658,"text":"is that wall tissues are doing so much more"},{"time":569754,"text":"than just covering the vascular tissues."},{"time":572257,"text":"They're an integral part of the penile skeleton."},{"time":575751,"text":"If the wall around the erectile tissue wasn't there,"},{"time":578288,"text":"if it wasn't reinforced in this way,"},{"time":580453,"text":"the shape would change,"},{"time":581605,"text":"but the inflated penis would not resist bending,"},{"time":583989,"text":"and erection simply wouldn't work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":586036,"text":"It's an observation with obvious medical applications"},{"time":588637,"text":"in humans as well,"},{"time":590419,"text":"but it's also relevant in a broad sense, I think,"},{"time":593354,"text":"to the design of prosthetics, soft robots,"},{"time":595786,"text":"basically anything"},{"time":596853,"text":"where changes of shape and stiffness are important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":600171,"text":"So to sum up:"},{"time":601919,"text":"Twenty years ago,"},{"time":603136,"text":"I had a college adviser tell me,"},{"time":604886,"text":"when I went to the college and said,"},{"time":606937,"text":"\"I'm kind of interested in anatomy,\""},{"time":608086,"text":"they said, \"Anatomy's a dead science.\"\n"},{"time":609970,"text":"He couldn't have been more wrong."},{"time":612587,"text":"I really believe that we still have a lot to learn"},{"time":615320,"text":"about the normal structure and function of our bodies."},{"time":618453,"text":"Not just about its genetics and molecular biology,"},{"time":621267,"text":"but up here in the meat end of the scale."},{"time":624666,"text":"We've got limits on our time."},{"time":626101,"text":"We often focus on one disease,"},{"time":628366,"text":"one model, one problem,"},{"time":629550,"text":"but my experience suggests"},{"time":631124,"text":"that we should take the time"},{"time":632902,"text":"to apply ideas broadly between systems"},{"time":635467,"text":"and just see where it takes us."},{"time":637341,"text":"After all, if ideas about invertebrate skeletons"},{"time":640941,"text":"can give us insights"},{"time":642407,"text":"about mammalian reproductive systems,"},{"time":644492,"text":"there could be lots of other wild and productive connections"},{"time":648541,"text":"lurking out there just waiting to be found."}]},{"cues":[{"time":650990,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":652842,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}